No problem! Let's add some simple visual debugging and a direct fix.

Quick Fix for Edit Button:

Replace the end of your editObservation() method with this simple version:

```javascript
        const recordBtn = document.getElementById('record-btn');
        if (recordBtn) {
            recordBtn.innerHTML = '<i class="fas fa-save"></i> Update Observation';
            recordBtn.dataset.editingId = id;
            recordBtn.onclick = () => this.handleUpdateObservation(id);
        }
        
        // SIMPLE TAB SWITCHING - No fancy function needed
        // 1. Update tab buttons
        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(btn => {
            btn.classList.remove('active');
            if (btn.getAttribute('data-tab') === 'record') {
                btn.classList.add('active');
            }
        });
        
        // 2. Update tab panels
        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(panel => {
            panel.classList.remove('active');
            panel.style.display = 'none';
            if (panel.id === 'record-panel') {
                panel.classList.add('active');
                panel.style.display = 'block';
            }
        });
        
        // 3. Add a visual indicator that we're editing
        const header = document.querySelector('.header');
        if (header) {
            header.style.boxShadow = '0 4px 20px rgba(46, 139, 87, 0.3)';
            header.style.borderBottom = '3px solid #2e8b57';
            
            // Remove the effect after 3 seconds
            setTimeout(() => {
                header.style.boxShadow = '';
                header.style.borderBottom = '';
            }, 3000);
        }
        
        // 4. Focus on the first field
        setTimeout(() => {
            if (observerNameInput) {
                observerNameInput.focus();
                observerNameInput.select(); // Also select the text
            }
            
            // Scroll to top on mobile
            if (window.innerWidth < 768) {
                window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
            }
        }, 100);
        
        // 5. Show a clear message
        this.showStatus(`✏️ Editing observation: ${id}`, 'info');
    },
```

This will:

1. ✅ Switch to the Record tab (visually and functionally)
2. ✅ Highlight the header so you can see it switched
3. ✅ Focus on the first field
4. ✅ Show a clear editing message
5. ✅ Work even if your switchTab() function has issues

If you want it even simpler:

Replace just the last 3 lines of your current editObservation() with:

```javascript
        const recordBtn = document.getElementById('record-btn');
        if (recordBtn) {
            recordBtn.innerHTML = '<i class="fas fa-save"></i> Update Observation';
            recordBtn.dataset.editingId = id;
            recordBtn.onclick = () => this.handleUpdateObservation(id);
        }
        
        // SIMPLE FIX: Manually switch tabs
        // Hide all panels
        document.getElementById('logbook-panel').classList.remove('active');
        document.getElementById('export-panel').classList.remove('active');
        
        // Show record panel
        document.getElementById('record-panel').classList.add('active');
        
        // Update tab buttons
        document.getElementById('tab-record').classList.add('active');
        document.getElementById('tab-logbook').classList.remove('active');
        document.getElementById('tab-export').classList.remove('active');
        
        if (observerNameInput) observerNameInput.focus();
    },
```

Add This CSS for Better Visual Feedback:

Add this to your CSS (anywhere in the style section):

```css
/* Visual feedback for editing mode */
body.editing-mode .header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e6b47 0%, #2e8b57 100%) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(46, 139, 87, 0.4) !important;
}

body.editing-mode .tab-btn[data-tab="record"] {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3) !important;
    color: white !important;
    font-weight: bold !important;
}
```

And update the JavaScript to toggle the class:

```javascript
// Add at the beginning of editObservation():
document.body.classList.add('editing-mode');

// Add when you're done editing (in handleUpdateObservation() or resetForm()):
document.body.classList.remove('editing-mode');
```

Try the simple fix first - it should work immediately without needing to debug anything!
